Program: Discovery
Title: First Technology - metals
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry40
Last Broadcast Date: 26 June 2002
How the manipulation of metals 10,000 years ago helped our ancestors. Naturally occuring metals such as native copper in the Middle East introduced the human race to the use of metals which was then made into both practical items, such as weapons, and also status materials - such as jewellery. Paul Craddock of the British Museum contributes. Show less